- aggregate sales price of securities in a successive 12-month period
  cannot exceed the greater of:

  1. $1M

  2. 15% of assets

  Rule 701(d)(2)

- must grant options within 10 years of plan adoption or approval

  10 CCR 260.140.41(f)

- must provide ... a copy of the compensatory benefit plan ...

  Rule 701(e)

- if the aggregate sales price over a successive 12-month period
  exceeds $5m, must make special disclosure

  Rule 701(e)
